dialogue: Why are your eyes so white?
Oh my God!!
How did you know?
In the park?
Just those two!
The receipt.
I don’t know.
Okay.
Wow!

Oh! You’re right. Oh God. But, before I can say ‘good-bye’, there’s something I really need you to know, Chandler. The way I feel about you, it’s like, I finally understand what Lionel Richie’s been singing about. Y'know, I mean what we have, it’s like movie love, you’re my soulmate, and I can’t believe we’re not going to be spending the rest of our lives together.
What?
No, you were right, you were right. I mean, I-I-I’ve got to give my marriage another chance.
Honey, honey, people are looking.
Janice has a question. Who of the six of you has sleep with the six of you?
Come on over the years none of you ever y'know, got drunk and stupid.
I’m sorry I find it hard to believe that a group of people who spends as much time together as you guys do has never bumped uglies.
Okay, okay, well then answer me this. Has any of you ever.... almost?
Uh-oh-okay. Uh-oh-okay. I know what you all are thinking. But Chandler is in Yemen! I'm a young woman! I have needs! I can't wait forever!
So I'm asking you please, take a moment before you judge me.
Actually, I should get going.
Yes! Yes! You did!
What is wrong now?!
I know! I know! And then you lose your apartment! And then you lose your job! And then your ex-wife gets married so fast! And now the coffee—ahh!! Ross, we need to talk.
No-no-no, no. I'm going to talk. I believe that the sun has set on our day in the sun.
Well yeah!!
Are you gonna be okay?
Okay.
So, who’s the lucky guy?
Oh. Oh I just cannot believe Clark stood me up!
Oh, what are you, stupid? It’s been three hours.
I should just go on to happier things, okay? Umm, why don’t you tell about your lovely wedding?
Oh…wait…you two think of me as family?! Oh, I have to ask you something now and be honest; do you want me to sing Careless Whisper or Lady In Red?
Chandler?
Please, it’s because otherwise I really don’t know what I might do.
Hey you guys, umm do either one of you want to get in there before I take my bath.
Why not?
Why?
He does?
Wait! Wait! I wanna see this. After I divorce him, half of that kingdom is gonna be mine.
Oh, I cannot believe he’s using our divorce to sell mattresses.
Oh my God.
Oh.... my.... God.
Oh.... my.... God.
By the way, Chandler. I cut you out of all my pictures. So if you want, I have a bag with just your heads.
Oh, are you sure? Really? Because you know, you could make little puppets out of them, and you could use them in your theater of cruelty.
Just us.
Although, I have enjoyed the fact that, uh your shirt's been stickin' outta your zipper ever since you came back from the bathroom.
So, do we have the best friends or what?
I will go for that drink.
Each.
Happy Valentine's Day!
Oh, I miss you already. Can you believe this happened?
Kiss me!
Hi, Monica.
This is so fun. This is like a reunion in the hall.
Hello, funny Valentine.
Hello, Joey, our little matchmaker. I could just kiss you all over, and I'm gonna!
I brought you something.
I had them made special.
That's fine.
Mmm-hmm. Because I know that this isn't the end.
No, it isn't, because you won't let that happen. Don't you know it yet? You love me, Chandler Bing.
Well then ask yourself this. Why do you think we keep ending up together? New Year's? Who invited who? Valentine's? Who asked who into whose bed?

You seek me out. Something deep in your soul calls out to me like a foghorn. Janice, Janice. You want me. You need me. You can't live without me. And you know it. You just don't know you know it. See ya.

I….can’t….believe this!
Oh y’know what? You have to speak very loudly when you’re talking to Sid, because he’s almost completely deaf.
So? Congratulations you two, I didn’t even know you got married.
What?!
Why?!!
Chandler Bing!
Oh, this should be easy. I have a very wide pelvis. You remember Chandler.
It’s you. This is yours.
He’s a keeper. How are you feeling?
Can I just say, I really admire what you’re doing. Just raising her all alone.
Oh, sure. Now. But what happens when he meets somebody else and gets married?
I’m telling you Rachel, listen to Janice. They all say they’re gonna be there until they start their real family.
Oh well that’s what I thought about my first husband, now I’m lucky if my kid gets to spend the weekend with her father and the twins and little Ms. New Boobs.
Oh hi!
Say hello to Aaron, your future son-in-law.
I’m gonna leave the three of you alone.
OH MY GOD!!
Ah ahahahhahaa! How great is this!
Well, Sid and I are trying again and we had trouble last time because apparently we...
Oh! Sid is still in his room. I don't allow porn at home so this is like a vacation for him. So did you do it? Did you make your deposit?
That's not the hard part honey! The hard part is what comes next, I mean aren't you worried about the results?
Oh! Well, you know what? It probably is.
Oh, Chandler, look. You and Monica are meant to have children. I am sure it's gonna be just fine.
What, you can do it in the parking lot of a Taco Bell, but you can't do it at a doctor's office?
Night-night Bing-a-ling.
Oh. God, crazy Chandler. He spun me...off...the...bed!
You know what, where he hugs you and kinda rolls you away and... Oh... my....God.
Oh my God!
What a small world!
Well... I just talked to Sid, we are definitely putting in an offer on the house... a-a-and I'll bet we get it.
Huh?
Oh... my...
Chandler, what are you talking about?
I don't know what to say... I mean, you know, obviously we have this... heat between us.
But I love my husband. And I know you love your wife. Now, I don't think we should get this house now.
Chandler, one of us has got to be strong.
Oh, no. Oh, no.
Oh, my, god.
Helloo!!
Hey, it's everybody.
Yes, I am.
Is it yours? Ha! You wish, Chandler Bing. You are looking at a married lady now.
Oh, sweetie, I'm sorry.
And what? Missed the expression on your face? Janice likes to have her fun.
Oh well, I’m divorced.
Bye.
Bye.
Bye.
Bye-bye.
Oh boy, I just love to sing!
I know! And I’m just getting out of a marriage, I mean talk about meant to be!
Oh, too soon, too schmoon. Face it honey, I am not letting you get away this time.
When?
Ugh, well I will just have to soak up every once of Chandler Bing until that moment comes.
Ohh, well when you said all you were going to be doing between now and the time you leave is packing, you didn’t really leave me much choice. Did you?
Okay, Chandler, come on!
Oh please. Every moment is precious. Y’know? Besides, somebody had to ride in that other taxi with the rest of your luggage, and your friends don’t really seem to care too much that you’re leaving.
On no! No! It’s not good-bye, I’m not leaving until you get on that plane.
What’s the matter? Is something wrong? Do you have to stay?
Oh, my Bing-a-ling. I’ll wait for you. Do you even know how long you’re going to be gone?
Chandler?
Chandler!
No! No! I wanna see you take-off.
What is the great tragedy here? You go get yourself another appointment.
So, how come you wanted to eat in tonight?
Oh, you didn't have to do this.
Well, I gotta buy a vowel. Because, oh my Gawd! Who, would've thought that someday, Chandler Bing would buy me a drawer.
We should?
You probably want us to move in together?
What are you doing here?
Are you being British?!
Why are you shopping here? You don't live in this neighborhood. Were you here waiting for me?
Barley? What kind of party serves barley?
Where is this party?
Who's party is it?
What woman?!
Oh, I wish. Look, honey, you have that report to finish, and I gotta go see my lawyer.
I'll see you later, sweetie. Bye Joey.
So, I hear, you hate me!
A little birdie told me something about you wanting to rip your arm off and throw it at me.
All right, fine, fine, fine, fine, fine, we've got to do something about our little situation here Joey. So, this is my idea: you and me spending some quality time together.
For Chandler!
Okay. All right. This is what we're gonna call it: 'Joey and Janice's DAY OF FUN!'
Yes, because that's how long it takes to love me.
We're baack!
